==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Goatsucker
<hw>Goat"suck`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>One of several species of insectivorous birds, belonging to
<gen>Caprimulgus</gen> and allied genera, esp. the European species
(<spn>Caprimulgus Europ⟦ae⟧us</spn>); -- so called from the mistaken
notion that it sucks goats. The European species is also
<altname>goat-milker</altname>, <altname>goat owl</altname>,
<altname>goat chaffer</altname>, <altname>fern owl</altname>,
<altname>night hawk</altname>, <altname>nightjar</altname>,
<altname>night churr</altname>, <altname>churr-owl</altname>,
<altname>gnat hawk</altname>, and <altname>dorhawk</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Goaves</ent>⟦br⟧
